The paper deals with deep learning-based detection and recognition of functional areas in indoor scenes, which involves computer vision (CV) and robotics (RO) applications. The paper also mentions the use of a testing-bed for evaluation, which suggests an emphasis on artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG). Additionally, the paper addresses the problem of scene understanding, which falls under the category of computer vision (CV) and could also be considered under the sub-category of cryptography and security (CR) due to the potential security implications of accurately identifying functional areas in indoor scenes.
